1
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:16,400
Lin Yaozu.

2
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,720
I have something to tell you.

3
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:19,680
Tell me.

4
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:22,080
I want to take you somewhere.

5
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:25,920
There are many historical records about overseas Chinese and the Nanqiao mechanics.

6
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,450
I think we can go take a look.

7
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:30,490
Maybe we can find the answers you're looking for.

8
00:01:31,039 --> 00:01:32,200
It's just that...

9
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,080
It's just that,

10
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:36,780
you don't know how I should face them.

11
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:40,400
Seeing this prosperous scene today,

12
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,920
what else can I not face?

13
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:45,520
I'm just afraid you won't want to go back.

14
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,039
All right.

15
00:01:48,039 --> 00:01:49,320
I've already rented a car.

16
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:50,920
Let's pack up and leave in a bit.

17
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:51,780
Are we driving?

18
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,120
I'm best at driving,

19
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:53,920
you know.

20
00:01:54,479 --> 00:01:56,539
I know you're an experienced driver.

21
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:58,920
But it's no longer the Anti-Japanese War era.

22
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,180
In peacetime, we need to abide by the law.

23
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,320
Not to mention you don't have a driver's license,

24
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,920
you don't even have an ID card.

25
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:06,320
I do.

26
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:06,980
Right here.

27
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:07,520
All right.

28
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:08,600
Put it away.

29
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:11,000
Just keep it as a souvenir.

30
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,840
The roads now are not

31
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,560
the kind of roads you came back on back then.

32
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,520
I can drive.

33
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,000
Should we call Yiyi?

34
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:20,960
I'll call her.

35
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,840
Zhang Xianzhi, look what time it is.

36
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:28,860
What time is it?

37
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,880
I think I really need to teach you a lesson

38
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,540
so you'll have a sense of time.

39
00:02:34,079 --> 00:02:35,400
Oh, I know.

40
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,200
I just have a lot of stuff.

41
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,760
Besides,

42
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,400
if you hadn't changed the itinerary at the last minute,

43
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,280
I'd still be in dreamland.

44
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:45,840
Punctuality is the first priority.

45
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,520
And you must do what you promised.

46
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:50,520
Oh, I know.

47
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,840
I'm coming down right now,

48
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:52,360
okay?

49
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,280
I'll definitely change next time.

50
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,010
Definitely.

51
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,400
Then hurry up.

52
00:02:59,000 --> 00:02:59,680
It's fine.

53
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:03,280
When she realizes the huge difference between one second and the next,

54
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:05,540
she will understand the concept of time.

55
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,720
Lin Yaozu,

56
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,120
you're so unobservant.

57
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,440
Come and give me a hand.

58
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,160
Coming.

59
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,240
I'm coming.

60
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:22,720
Give it to me.

61
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:30,880
You two are so sweet,

62
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:31,880
ah,

63
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,840
making me pack so many things.

64
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:36,320
Let's go.

65
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,120
Hey.

66
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,360
Remember to fasten your seat belts.

67
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,320
Ready.

68
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,079
Let's go.

69
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,040
Hey,

70
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,240
do you want to know

71
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:26,320
how we identified spies back then?

72
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:29,360
There were spies in transportation back then?

73
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:29,960
Of course.

74
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,960
When we first returned to China for training,

75
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:32,800
we were warned

76
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,260
never to lust after women.

77
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:37,320
Shouldn't you be on guard against the Japanese army?

78
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:39,720
Why were you warned not to lust after women?

79
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,880
Spies were part of the Japanese army.

80
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,200
Besides,

81
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,800
lust leads to trouble.

82
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:48,520
To sabotage us,

83
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,120
the Japanese army planted many female spies

84
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,560
around us to gather intelligence.

85
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,440
Back then,

86
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:54,600
many military supplies were burned.

87
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:58,040
These female spies even used honey traps.

88
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,480
But it's no wonder.

89
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,760
You were all hot-blooded young men.

90
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,480
But with such temptation,

91
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,040
could you resist it?

92
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:10,200
Back then, to achieve their goals, the Japanese army

93
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:12,200
would use any means necessary.

94
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,320
At first, we were curious too

95
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:19,280
why the Japanese army could accurately bomb Gongguo Bridge over ten times.

96
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:22,120
How did they know our exact departure information?

97
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:25,120
Did someone among you fall for the honey trap?

98
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:26,560
Not quite.

99
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,880
It was because one time,

100
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,400
a beggar-like person

101
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,920
kept sneaking behind our convoy,

102
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,520
which caught our attention.

103
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:51,760
Stop!

104
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,280
Why are you following me?

105
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,530
Why are you running?

106
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,920
In this wartime,

107
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,240
it's dangerous to be chased!

108
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,440
Dangerous?

109
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,500
I think you're the dangerous one.

110
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:07,760
What are you talking about?

111
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,800
I don't understand.

112
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,760
I've never seen a begging beggar

113
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,180
with such clean hands.

114
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:12,760
Go.

115
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,600
Come with me.

116
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,040
Oh,

117
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,480
I see.

118
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:23,120
With her soft and fair skin,

119
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,640
she didn't look like a beggar at all.

120
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,480
What an unprofessional spy.

121
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,140
Bad review.

122
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,120
Those spies,

123
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,520
let alone being beggars,

124
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,840
if they could endure half the elements we did,

125
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:33,800
it would be impressive.

126
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,600
Also,

127
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,000
when you buy things now,

128
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,200
you don't even use money.

129
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,120
You use that...

130
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:38,960
what do you call it?

131
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,440
Cell... cell phone.

132
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:40,840
Oh.

133
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,200
Stop.

134
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,320
It's not that we don't use cash,

135
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,560
we just use it less.

136
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:46,290
We use mobile payments now.

137
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,040
Mobile payments.

138
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,480
When we bought things back then,

139
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:51,680
we also had different payment methods.

140
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,480
How different?

141
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,080
Did you buy on credit?

142
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,280
Honesty is the most important quality.

143
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:58,740
How could we buy on credit?

144
00:06:58,760 --> 00:06:59,760
We bought if we had money,

145
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,160
and didn't if we had none.

146
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,920
It's because I remember one time,

147
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:06,960
we passed by a place called Xiaodong Village.

148
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,300
How much is this, boss?

149
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,120
50 cents.

150
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:15,280
You two look like mechanics.

151
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,160
I don't have change.

152
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,280
Ah,

153
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,320
thanks.

154
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:30,560
How about this?

155
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,450
Use this 50 cents next time.

156
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,320
Thank you, boss.

157
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:39,800
Thank you, boss.

158
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,360
Thanks.

159
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:41,680
Goodbye.

160
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,280
Mechanic.

161
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:45,400
What's going on here?

162
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:49,240
Because the store owner knew we were mechanics returning home to transport goods.

163
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:51,360
There are already too many uncertainties on the road,

164
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,760
and we are pressed for time,

165
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:54,440
so they came up with this idea.

166
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,480
Then that boss is pretty nice.

167
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,080
Xiao Ai.

168
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,520
Driver, please speak.

169
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,240
Navigate to a charging station.

170
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,840
Which one do you want to go to?

171
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:09,400
Set this as the destination or a waypoint?

172
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,720
Destination updated.

173
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,440
Turn left into the internal road in 70 meters.

174
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:14,440
Wow,

175
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,840
this is amazing.

176
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,400
Now.

177
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,600
Isn't it amazing?

178
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:19,040
Yaozu,

179
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:21,240
you were staring at that charging station just now.

180
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,040
Is there a problem?

181
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,040
What problem could there be?

182
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,320
He must be curious.

183
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:29,370
He must be thinking about his transport journey.

184
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,440
These things you have now

185
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,720
are really convenient.

186
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,320
And it won't leak out either.

187
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,080
Leak out?

188
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,880
That would be terrible if it leaked.

189
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,440
That's a safety issue.

190
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:43,880
Back when we used to pour gasoline into cars,

191
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:45,200
we had to be very careful,

192
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,400
afraid it would leak.

193
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:49,850
Back then, a drop of gasoline was like a drop of blood.

194
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:51,720
That's an exaggeration.

195
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,760
Exaggeration?

196
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:53,640
You must know,

197
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,960
if the transport trucks ran out of gasoline,

198
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,690
they would be like scrap metal.

199
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,360
Not only was it not enough,

200
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,760
but we also had to save it.

201
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:03,420
Sometimes gasoline couldn't even be supplied.

202
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:04,810
Then what did you do?

203
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,440
So some mechanics tried every means

204
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,600
to save as much as possible.

205
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:11,280
Try to control the throttle as much as possible when driving.

206
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,280
Some mechanics

207
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,320
even came up with the idea

208
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,450
of using charcoal to start the engine.

209
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,770
Isn't that returning to the steam age?

210
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,090
Pretty much.

211
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,610
Although the method was feasible,

212
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:25,080
the power was indeed barely satisfactory.

213
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,200
What's going on?

214
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,520
Where is it ringing?

215
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:33,840
It's nothing.

216
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:34,920
The tire pressure is too low.

217
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,050
Let's go take a look.

218
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:37,120
Tire pressure is too low.
